Police officers from the EThekwini Central Cluster Task Team arrested the three suspects aged between 29 and 36 with a large quantity of cigarettes in their possession. The trio paid a R1,000 bail each and they will appear in the Durban Magistrate’s Court in August. Police spokesperson, Brigadier Jay Naicker said, “Police pounced on the suspects at a building on Prince Street in the Point policing precinct after holding observation on the building. During the operation, 71 boxes of tobacco, prescription drugs and illicit cigarettes were recovered. The recovered items are estimated to be approximately R800, 000 in value.” “The suspects were charged for dealing in illicit cigarettes and dealing in prescription contraband. They were released on R1, 000 bail each and will appear in the Durban Magistrates Court on 6 August 2020,” Brig Naicker added. The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula commended the police officers for their diligence in maintaining law and order.